Michele & Gene Cornelius wrote-
Date: Tuesday, August 07, 2001 1:53 AM
Subject: [VB] Hydraulic tappets?

>It was mentioned to me that it is possible that the PO might have put
>hydraulic tappets in this beast.  How do I find out?  Maybe they put a
>crazy-lift cam in, and the extra motion is what is making all the noise, but
>short of pulling the engine, yanking the heads off, and sticking an eyestalk
>into the bores, how can I tell?

Pull the oil pump and you will see rivets on a stock camshaft, while a
"crazy" cam will have hex bolts attaching the gear to the camshaft.
Dave Wolfanger



